<main class="shell page-grid reveal">
  <section class="content-flow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Windows</p>
    <h2>Microsoft Windows is one of the most widely used operating systems for personal and business computing.</h2>
    <p>Windows is developed by Microsoft and is known for its broad software compatibility, familiar desktop interface, and long history of use in homes, schools, and offices.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-flow">
    <h3>Main features</h3>
    <div class="project-list">
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Graphical user interface</strong><p>Windows is designed to be approachable for general users through a familiar desktop environment.</p></article>
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Strong software support</strong><p>Many common applications and games are developed with Windows compatibility in mind.</p></article>
      <article class="project-item"><strong>Enterprise integration</strong><p>Windows is often used in organizations because of its connection to Microsoft business tools and services.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-flow statement-band">
    <p class="eyebrow">Recent versions</p>
    <h3>Windows 10 and Windows 11 show how the platform continues to change over time.</h3>
    <p>Windows 10 introduced features such as virtual desktops, while Windows 11 focused more on visual redesign and interface refinement.</p>
  </section>
</main>

